1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
A complete workflow from image generation
to editing and archiving.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,950
We begin with a new task in Codex,
then generate images directly on the Cowart canvas.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,700
Three different visual styles appear in sequence.

4
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:29,804
Each image can be selected, moved, resized,
and rearranged directly on the canvas.

5
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,400
Once generation is complete,
every asset is automatically added to MOSA.

6
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:54,220
The gallery brings all results together,
while preserving the prompt, model, dimensions, and source.

7
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,300
Next, we return to Codex and create
architectural, fashion, and material studies.

8
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:19,017
Different formats and mediums all remain
part of the same workflow.

9
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,100
Each artwork can be opened on its own
and reviewed in detail.

10
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:49,256
Refine it further, or save it directly
to the library.

11
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,200
Finally, MOSA reconnects the work
created across Codex and Cowart,

12
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:13,748
while keeping every source and parameter traceable.

13
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,600
From generation and editing
to archiving and reuse,

14
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,238
the entire creative pipeline is complete.
